==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homeopathy
<hw>Ho*me*op"a*thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
likeness of condition or feeling; <?/ like (fr. <?/ same; cf.
<er>Same</er>) + <?/ to suffer: cf. F. <ets>hom⟦eacute⟧opathie</ets>.
See <er>Pathos</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The art of curing,
founded on resemblances; the theory and its practice that disease is
cured (<xex>tuto</xex>, <xex>cito</xex>, <xex>et jucunde</xex>) by
remedies which produce on a healthy person effects similar to the
symptoms of the complaint under which the patient suffers, the remedies
being usually administered in minute doses. This system was founded by
<person>Dr. Samuel Hahnemann</person>, and is opposed to
<contr>allopathy</contr>, or <contr>heteropathy</contr>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hom⟦oe⟧opathy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

